<%# Registration page wrapper with privacy, payment visibility and account safety messaging %>
<div class="container py-4 register-page">
  <div class="register-hero mb-4">
    <div>
      <p class="register-eyebrow mb-1">Create your PokeValue account</p>
      <h1 class="mb-2">Register</h1>
      <p class="register-hero-text mb-0">
        Create a private account for tracking your portfolio, joining the marketplace, hosting auctions and joining raffles.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="row g-4">
    <div class="col-lg-7">
      <%= render "registrations/form" %>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-5">
      <%# Safety notice explaining what users should avoid putting into their account details %>
      <div class="register-info-card mb-3">
        <h2>Account Safety Notice</h2>
        <p>
          Do not use your real name as your username or password. Choose a username that does not personally identify you.
        </p>
        <p>
          Your password should be unique to PokeValue and should not be reused from another website or application.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-0">
          PokeValue will never ask you to enter your real name during registration.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# Payment visibility notice explaining how the Revolut tag is reused later by the platform %>
      <div class="register-info-card register-warning-card mb-3">
        <h2>Revolut Tag Visibility Notice</h2>
        <p>
          Your Revolut tag is collected during registration because it is used later for marketplace, auction and raffle payment flows.
        </p>
        <p>
          When you create a listing, host an auction or host a raffle, the system may automatically display your registered Revolut tag to the buyer, winning bidder or raffle ticket buyer when payment is required.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-0">
          Only register with a Revolut tag that you are comfortable being shown to other users during payment-related actions.
        </p>
      </div>

      <%# Security notice avoids promising perfect protection while explaining the measures used by the app %>
      <div class="register-info-card">
        <h2>Security Notice</h2>
        <p>
          PokeValue uses password hashing, session management, admin MFA, account lockout rules and encrypted Revolut tag storage to reduce account and payment-detail risk.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-0">
          No web application can guarantee complete protection from every possible security issue. Users should avoid entering personal information that is not required.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>